The clean interface & large keys are the main pluses, but they are in part due to this calculator's limited functionalities. Support just one memory variable, no support for user-defined constants, and you cannot select results (although you can select a previous operation) from history & perform another operation with them! Big deal that the backspace key works as it *should* but even though it runs on touchscreen devices there is no free editing; if you entered 1233567 instead of 1234567 you can't just delete the 3 and enter 4. What's more, it is *slow* to be ready even if it was already in memory & even after the latest update!! No theme changing, and occasionally reminds you to rate this app. Never mind the hype, deserves a rating no more than 3.5-4 out of 5.
